I"º<p>In a similar way in which <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/gaze-stabilization-is-preprocessing-in-vision">gaze movements stabilize the orientation of the image being projected onto the retina</a>, the pupil light response stabilizes the brightness of the image. The pupil light response is merely tasked with acting as a buffer, maintaining isoluminance for a short period, while the eye-level chemical adaptations kick in.</p>
